com.cognifide.slice.api.execution

Interface ExecutionContextStack

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExecutionContextStackImpl
    Deprecated. 
    This interface will be hidden from public use in next major version. Use ModelProvider instead.

    @ProviderType
 @Deprecated
public interface ExecutionContextStack
    Execution context stack of Slice Injector. New ExecutionContext is put on this stack each time a new call to ModelProvider is made. After call is finished the ExecutionContext is taken from this stack. This allows Slice to build recursively complex models that need to have other models injected or changing a scope of current resource by using ModelProvider in client code.

      • getAbsolutePath

        String getAbsolutePath(String path)
        Deprecated. 
        Parameters:
        path - path to be transformed
        Returns:
        absolute path from given path. If path is already absolute then it will be returned unchanged. If it is relative (starting with ./) then it will be appended (after removing ./) to path of current top of this stack. InvalidExecutionContextException with be thrown in case when stack is empty and path is relative.
